issue_body:
Mustache template syntax HTML-escapes values by default (see https://mustache.github.io/mustache.5.html):

> All variables are HTML escaped by default. If you want to return unescaped HTML, use the triple mustache: {{{name}}}.

All of our documentation, however, seems to show double brace examples. Arguably, the majority of ingest pipelines probably want non-escaped values. Without using triple brace we get behavior that looks like the following:

```zsh
➜  ~ curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" -s -X POST \
-u elastic:password http://localhost:9200/_ingest/pipeline/_simulate\?verbose \
--data-binary @- << 'EOF' | jq
{
  "pipeline": {
    "processors": [
      {
        "set": {
          "field": "foo",
          "value": "{{bar}}"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "docs": [
    {
      "_source": {
        "bar": "\\"
      }
    }
  ]
}
EOF
{
  "docs": [
    {
      "processor_results": [
        {
          "processor_type": "set",
          "status": "success",
          "doc": {
            "_index": "_index",
            "_id": "_id",
            "_source": {
              "bar": "\\",
              "foo": "\\\\"
            },
            "_ingest": {
              "pipeline": "_simulate_pipeline",
              "timestamp": "2021-04-06T15:51:02.759992Z"
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Notice the double escaping of the backslash that's already escaped.

Here's what is likely wanted in this example:

```zsh
➜  ~ curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" -s -X POST \
-u elastic:password http://localhost:9200/_ingest/pipeline/_simulate\?verbose \
--data-binary @- << 'EOF' | jq
{
  "pipeline": {
    "processors": [
      {
        "set": {
          "field": "foo",
          "value": "{{{bar}}}"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "docs": [
    {
      "_source": {
        "bar": "\\"
      }
    }
  ]
}
EOF
{
  "docs": [
    {
      "processor_results": [
        {
          "processor_type": "set",
          "status": "success",
          "doc": {
            "_index": "_index",
            "_id": "_id",
            "_source": {
              "bar": "\\",
              "foo": "\\"
            },
            "_ingest": {
              "pipeline": "_simulate_pipeline",
              "timestamp": "2021-04-06T15:52:00.865879Z"
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

It's a pretty easy mistake to make, but we don't call it out in the docs either as an example or with explicit text. We should.

